Police officers raided properties last week where they also arrested 203 people and seized 10 illegal firearms. CAPE TOWN Western Cape police say they've shut down at least 96 drug dens during operations in the Nyanga cluster.Police officers, supported by metro police, raided the properties last week where they also arrested 203 people and seized 10 illegal firearms.They also confiscated 95 units of Heroine, more than 300 of tik and 140 mandrax tablets. In a separate incident, 3 people were arrested for the murder of a 23-year-old in Nyanga's Crossroads. The police's Frederick van Wyk said, Three suspects were arrested two days later. All suspects face charges of murder, hijacking and possession of illegal weapon. 